## Diagnosing & Fixing Node.js Memory Leaks

### Find the leak first

```bash
# Built-in heap snapshot (Node 11+)
node --inspect app.js
# Open chrome://inspect → Memory → Take heap snapshot → compare over time

# Or programmatically
const v8 = require('v8');
const fs = require('fs');
fs.writeFileSync('heap.heapsnapshot', JSON.stringify(v8.writeHeapSnapshot()));
```

```bash
# Track memory over time
node --max-old-space-size=512 app.js  # forces GC pressure, reveals leaks faster
```

### Common causes & fixes

**1. Event listener accumulation**
```js
// Bad — adds new listener every request
emitter.on('data', handler);

// Fix
emitter.once('data', handler);         // auto-removes
// or
emitter.removeListener('data', handler); // manual cleanup
emitter.setMaxListeners(20);           // raises warning threshold
```

**2. Closures holding references**
```js
// Bad — cache grows unbounded
const cache = {};
app.get('/item/:id', (req, res) => {
  cache[req.params.id] = fetchData(); // never evicted
});

// Fix — use LRU or TTL cache
const LRU = require('lru-cache');
const cache = new LRU({ max: 500, ttl: 1000 * 60 * 5 });
```

**3. Timers not cleared**
```js
// Bad
setInterval(pollDB, 1000); // runs forever even after "shutdown"

// Fix
const timer = setInterval(pollDB, 1000);
process.on('SIGTERM', () => clearInterval(timer));
```

**4. Global/module-level accumulation**
```js
// Bad
global.logs = [];
app.use((req) => global.logs.push(req)); // unbounded

// Fix — cap size or use streams/rotating logs
```

**5. Unclosed streams/connections**
```js
// Always destroy streams on error
stream.on('error', (err) => stream.destroy());
// Always close DB connections in finally blocks
```

### Monitor in production

```bash
# Built-in report on OOM
node --report-on-fatalerror app.js

# Process memory via code
setInterval(() => {
  const { heapUsed, heapTotal } = process.memoryUsage();
  console.log(`Heap: ${(heapUsed/1024/1024).toFixed(1)}MB / ${(heapTotal/1024/1024).toFixed(1)}MB`);
}, 30_000);
```

### Tools

| Tool | Use |
|------|-----|
| `node --inspect` + Chrome DevTools | Heap snapshots, allocation timeline |
| `clinic.js` (`npx clinic doctor`) | Automated leak diagnosis |
| `memwatch-next` | Emits events on heap growth |
| `heapdump` | Programmatic snapshots in prod |

### Quick wins checklist

- [ ] All `EventEmitter` listeners removed when object destroyed
- [ ] All `setInterval`/`setTimeout` cleared on shutdown  
- [ ] Caches have max size + TTL
- [ ] Streams closed/destroyed on error
- [ ] DB/Redis connections pooled, not created per-request
- [ ] No unbounded arrays/maps at module scope

The most effective approach: **take two heap snapshots 5 minutes apart**, diff them in Chrome DevTools → look for objects with growing "Retained Size."
